Mozambique is regularly affected by natural disasters, including floods, drought and cyclones.
Tropical Storm Eloise may bring hazardous sea and weather conditions to Central and Southern Mozambique from Saturday 23 January 2020. Monitor local reports and international weather updates from the World Meteorological Organisation, check your routes before travelling around the country and follow the advice of the local authorities.
